.TH "tlb_gather_mmu_fullmm" 9 "tlb_gather_mmu_fullmm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tlb_gather_mmu_fullmm \- initialize an mmu_gather structure for page-table tear-down
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" tlb_gather_mmu_fullmm
.BI "(struct mmu_gather *tlb "  ","
.BI "struct mm_struct *mm "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tlb" 12
the mmu_gather structure to initialize
.IP "mm" 12
the mm_struct of the target address space
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
In this case, \fImm\fP is without users and we're going to destroy the
full address space (exit/execve).

Called to initialize an (on-stack) mmu_gather structure for page-table
tear-down from \fImm\fP.
